title: cj71nm-dy-r2b
memo: DY injection at the apex of the frontal pole, contained within area 10. Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 6 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712—1737).
case_memo: Animal was part of a study centred on the connections of the frontal pole cortex.

title: cj70x-dy-r2c
memo: DY injection at the apex of the frontal pole (area 10). Manual reconstruction of this case has been illustrated in Figure 7 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712-1737).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of prefrontal cortex. It received 4 injections, but the FE injection in the rostral part of area 47L resulted in too few labeled neurones, hence not being suitable for quantitative analyses.

title: cj71nm-fb-r2d
memo: FB injection in the lateral part of the frontopolar cortex (area 10). Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 8 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712—1737).
case_memo: Animal was part of a study centred on the connections of the frontal pole cortex.

title: cj71r-dy-r2b
memo: DY injection at the apex of the frontal pole, contained within area 10. Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 6 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712—1737).
case_memo: Animal was part of a study centred on the connections of the frontal pole cortex.

title: cj71r-fb-r2d
memo: FB injection in the lateral part of the frontopolar cortex (area 10). Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 8 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712—1737).
case_memo: Animal was part of a study centred on the connections of the frontal pole cortex.

title: cj73nm-fr-r4b
memo: FR injection along the medial surface of the frontopolar cortex (area 10). Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 4 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712—1737).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj73x-fr-r4b
memo: FR injection along the medial surface of the frontopolar cortex (area 10). Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 4 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712—1737).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj178-ctbr-r3a
memo: The CTB-red injection was located in the most caudal part of area 10 (frontopolar cortex).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study of prefrontal cortex connections, but also had an attempted injection in the peripheral representation of V1.

title: cj178-ctbgr-r3a
memo: The CTB-green injection was located in the most caudal part of area 10 (frontopolar cortex). It may have invaded area 46 to a slight extent, particularly in the infragranular layers (e.g. section r4a).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study of prefrontal cortex connections, but also had an attempted injection in the peripheral representation of V1.

title: cj70x-fe-r6a
memo: FE injection not displayed
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of prefrontal cortex. It received 4 injections, but the FE injection in the rostral part of area 47L resulted in too few labeled neurones, hence not being suitable for quantitative analyses.

title: cj71nm-fr-r5b
memo: FR injection in the rostral part of area 47L (12L). Minimal to no invasion of adjacent areas.
case_memo: Animal was part of a study centred on the connections of the frontal pole cortex.

title: cj73nm-fb-r7b
memo: Registration of the FB injection data to the Paxinos et al. (2012) atlas template indicates that it was located near the junction of areas 47L (12L) and 46V, with the majority of the injection being in 47L. This assessment is supported by the complex pattern of label that probably includes afferents to both areas. Results from this injection were shown in Figures 9 and 10 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712--1737) as being assigned to area 46; this pre-dates the more comprehensive analysis of the frontal lobe cytoarchitecture by Paxinos et al, (2012).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj71r-fr-r5b
memo: FR injection in the rostral part of area 47L (12L); no apparent invasion of adjacent areas.
case_memo: Animal was part of a study centred on the connections of the frontal pole cortex.

title: cj800nm-fb-r9b
memo: The FB injection was small and restricted to layers 1, 2 and upper 3. It was centred in the rostral part of area 47L, with possible involvement of area 8aV. However the absence of label in visual cortex suggests that 8aV was not part of the effective injection site.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj181nm-dy-r4c
memo: The DY injection involved all layers of the rostral part of area 47L. Little to no involvement of area 46V by the halo.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj215-ctbr-r8b
memo: The CTB-red injection was contained in the area 47L (12L) of the  ventrolateral prefrontal cortex. The majority of the tracer was deposited in the supragranular layers
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective tracer injections

title: cj73x-fb-r7b
memo: Registration of the FB injection data to the Paxinos et al. (2012) atlas template indicates that it was located near the junction of areas 47L (12L), 8aV and 46V. This assessment is supported by the complex pattern of label that probably includes afferents to all 3 areas. Results from this injection were shown in Figures 9 and 10 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712--1737) as being assigned to area 46; this pre-dates the more comprehensive analysis of the frontal lobe cytoarchitecture by Paxinos et al, (2012).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj181-dy-r4c
memo: The DY injection involved all layers of area 47L. It was restricted to the rostral part of this area.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj800-fb-r9b
memo: The FB injection was small and restricted to the supragranular layers. It was centred in the rostral part of area 47L. The injection "halo" may have invaded area 8aV, but the absence of label in visual cortex suggested that this was not part of the effective injection site.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj213-ctbr-r9a
memo: The CTBr injection was largely contained in the rostral part of area 47L (12L). Invasion of area 8aV, if occurred, was only in the infragranular layers. near its caudal end.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections, including 2 in the ventrolateral prefrontal cortex and 2 in somatomotor cortex

title: cj213-dy-r10b
memo: The DY injection was contained in the rostral part of area 47l(12l). Possible encroachment into area 8aV by the halo was minimal if existent.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections, including 2 in the ventrolateral prefrontal cortex and 2 in somatomotor cortex

title: cj73nm-fe-r11b
memo: FE injection centred in area 47L (12L). Likely involvement of the supragranular layers of area 45.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj73x-fe-r11b
memo: FE injection centred in area 47L (12L). The presence of label in extrastriate cortex suggests involvement of cytoarchitectural area 45, which in marmosets is part of the putative frontal eye field (Reser et al. 2013;  Cereb Cortex  23:1901–1922).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj227-dy-r7b
memo: The DY injection was largely restricted to the caudal part of area 47 lateral (47L), with possible small involvement of area 45.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but one (CTBg) did not result in long-distance label. There were some problems during the sectioning, resulting in the rostral block not being sectioned exactly in the coronal plane.

title: cj800nm-dy-r8a
memo: The DY injection crossed from dorsal area 46 (46D) into area 10.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj204r-fb-r4a
memo: The FB injection was entered on the border between areas 9 and 32. The pattern of label was very similar to that revealed by other injections in area 9

title: cj205-ctbr-r5b
memo: The CTB-red injection was in medial prefrontal cortex, centred in area 9 but with some involvement of the dorsal part of area 32 long the midline. The pattern of label was very similar to that revealed by another area 9 injection (CJ70-FB), in terms of main regions of cortical label, but included additional label in the caudal orbitofrontal cortex and anterior insular cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj181nm-ctbr-r3d
memo: The CTB-red injection was restricted to area 11 of the rostral orbitofrontal cortex. There was no noticeable leakage up the track into dorsolateral prefrontal cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj800-dy-r8a
memo: The DY injection was small, and restricted to area 46 dorsal (46D).
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj214-ctbr-r4b
memo: The CTBr injection was located primarily in the lateral part of area 46V. The borders of areas in this region follow a complex trajectory, so invasion of the rostral part of area 47L (12L) is likely.
case_memo: This animal had 4 good injections, 2 in prefrontal cortex (CTBr and DY), 1 in posterior parietal cortex (CTBg) and 1 in visual area MT (FB)

title: cj181-ctbr-r3d
memo: The CTB-red injection was restricted to area 11 of the rostral orbitofrontal cortex. There was no noticeable leakage up the track into dorsolateral prefrontal cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj801-dy-r4d
memo: DY injection centred in area 46D (dorsal), involving all layers.
case_memo: This animal had 3 effective injections in the frontal cortex. There was also a failed attempt to inject area 11 with CTB-red (track visible in section r6c).

title: cj70x-fb-r8a
memo: FB injection restricted to area 9 (caudal part).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of prefrontal cortex. It received 4 injections, but the FE injection in the rostral part of area 47L resulted in too few labeled neurones, hence not being suitable for quantitative analyses.

title: cj227-ctbr-r6d
memo: The CTB-red injection was centred on area 47 medial (47M) but likely also involved parts of area 47 lateral (47L).
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but one (CTBg) did not result in long-distance label. There were some problems during the sectioning, resulting in the rostral block not being sectioned exactly in the coronal plane.

title: cj178-dy-r6a
memo: The DY injection in medial frontal cortex was well centred in area 32. The extent of the injection halo suggests that there may have been a slight contamination of area 8b, but the pattern of label does not reveal widespread intrinsic connections within the latter area.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study of prefrontal cortex connections, but also had an attempted injection in the peripheral representation of V1.

title: cj148r-dy-r6a
memo: The DY injection was very restricted and left no tracer leakage up the track. It was well centred in area 32V (also known as area 10mc; e.g. as in Burman and Rosa 2009; J Comp Neurol 514:11–29).
case_memo: This case had a single successful injection in the right hemisphere (DY).

title: cj227-ctbgr-r7a
memo: The CTB-green injection was largely ineffective, labelling only local connections. It was located in th caudal most part of area 32.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but one (CTBg) did not result in long-distance label. There were some problems during the sectioning, resulting in the rostral block not being sectioned exactly in the coronal plane.

title: cj214-dy-r5c
memo: The DY injection was centred in area 8aD, with no apparent invasion of adjacent areas
case_memo: This animal had 4 good injections, 2 in prefrontal cortex (CTBr and DY), 1 in posterior parietal cortex (CTBg) and 1 in visual area MT (FB)

title: cj204r-ctbgr-r6c
memo: The CTB green injection was located in the rostral part of area 8aD, away from both areas 8b and 8aV. The border region with area 46D was approached, but involvement of the latter is unlikely.

title: cj800nm-ctbr-r12a
memo: The CTB-red was centred in cytoarchitectural area 8aD, and involved all layers. Part of the halo may have included the lower layers of area 46D.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj800-ctbr-r12a
memo: The CTB-red was centred in cytoarchitectural area 8aD, and involved all layers with no apparent invasion of adjacent areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj70x-fr-r10a
memo: The FR injection was located in the rostral part of frontal area 8aD. This injection was part of the study published by Reser et al. 2013 (Cereb Cortex  23:1901–1922).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of prefrontal cortex. It received 4 injections, but the FE injection in the rostral part of area 47L resulted in too few labeled neurones, hence not being suitable for quantitative analyses.

title: cj205-dy-r10b
memo: The DY injection was centred in dorsolateral prefrontal area 8aD. This was the largest 8aD injection, and its halo is likely to have invaded area 8aV. This has revealed additional labeled regions compared to other injections in 8aD.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj108-fr-r11a
memo: FR injection consisted of 2 parallel tracks in area 8aD. CARET reconstruction also illustrated in Fig. 4B or Reser et al. 2013.
case_memo: This animal was part of a project on the connections of caudal dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (area 8)

title: cj74-fr-r10b
memo: FR injection in area 8aV, with possible minor (halo) involvement of area 47L.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of marmoset caudal prefrontal cortex, focused on subdivisions of area 8.

title: cj108-fe-r10a
memo: FE injection in area 8aV (frontal eye field). CARET reconstruction illustrated in Fig. 4C of Reser et al. 2013 (Cereb Cortex 23: 1901–1922). Comparison between manual and automated reconstructions illustrated in Fig. 9 of Majka et al. 2016 (J Comp Neurol 524:2161–2181).
case_memo: This animal was part of a project on the connections of caudal dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (area 8)

title: cj75x-dy-r14b
memo: DY injection in the ventral part of cytoarchitectural area 8aV, with invasion of area 45. Extensive label in visual areas interpreted as indicating that it involved the central visual field (small saccade) part of the frontal eye field. This injection was illustrated in the paper by Reser et al. 2013 (Cereb Cortex 23: 1901-1922)
case_memo: Case with 2 good injections (FR and DY). There was ischemic damage to the dorsal surface.

title: cj125x-fr-r14a
memo: FR injection in area 8aV (frontal eye field).
case_memo: This animal had 2 tracer injections (FE and FR) in the dorsolateral surface of the caudal frontal cortex.

title: cj94-dy-r16b
memo: DY injection in the ventral part of the frontal eye field (area 8aV) wit likely halo crossing into more ventral cortex (area 45 or area 6Va. Manual reconstruction shown in Fig. 4D of Reser et al. 2013 (Cereb Cortex 23: 1901–1922).
case_memo: Animal with multiple injections in the caudal part of the frontal lobe.

title: cj73x-dy-r10b
memo: DY injection in area 8b. Results from this injection were shown in Figures 9 and 10 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712--1737). At that time the injection was estimated to be in area 9.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj73nm-dy-r10b
memo: DY injection in area 8b, primarily including the supragranular layers. Results from this injection were shown in Figures 9 and 10 of Burman et al. 2011 (Cereb Cortex 21:1712--1737). At that time the injection was estimated to be in area 9.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of the rostral prefrontal cortex. It had 4 tracer injections.

title: cj164-dy-r6d
memo: DY injection was well restricted to area 8b, close to the midline.
case_memo: This animal had 3 good injections in the medial frontal cortex

title: cj74-fb-r12b
memo: FB injection centred in area 8b. Data were summarised in Reser et al. 2013 (Cereb Cortex  23:1901–1922).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of marmoset caudal prefrontal cortex, focused on subdivisions of area 8.

title: cj163-dy-r13a
memo: DY injection in area 8b.
case_memo:
This animal had 4 injections in the medial frontal lobe: FB and DY in the left hemisphere and CTB (red and green) in the right. The injections reconstructed here are the FB and DY (images were flipped so injections appear on the right, to facilitate comparison with other cars). 

This animal also underwent electrophysiological recordings in extrastriate cortex. This resulted in some herniation and electrode tracks, visible for example in the neighbourhood of section c26b.

title: cj215-ctbgr-r14a
memo: The CTB-green injection primarily involved the supragranular and granular layers of area 45, but there was involvement of adjacent area 47L (12L).
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective tracer injections

title: cj800nm-ctbgr-r16a
memo: The CTB-green was centred in cytoarchitectural area 45, but invaded area 47L to some extent. The pattern of label included central vision representations in visual cortex, as expected from the results of an earlier study (Reser et al. 2013, Cereb Cortex 23:1901–1922).
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj800-ctbgr-r16a
memo: The CTB-green was centred in cytoarchitectural area 45, but invaded area 47L to some extent. The pattern of label included central vision representations in visual cortex, as expected from the results of an earlier study (Reser et al. 2013, Cereb Cortex 23:1901–1922).
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the frontal lobe. The cytoarchitectural analysis used the NeuN stain. The results in this case are not particularly clear at low power due to low differentiation, but the stain was successful and cytoarchitectural features can be analysed at high magnification.

title: cj83-dy-r13b
memo: DY injection in caudal area 8b. CARET reconstruction illustrated in Figure 4A of Reser et al. 2013 (Cereb Cortex 23: 1901–1922).
case_memo: Case discussed in detail in Majka et al. (2016; J Comp Neurol 524:2161–2181) as one in which there is significant discrepancy in the location of injection site as estimated by manual and automated reconstruction methods. Note discrepancy between yellow circles in flat map (small circle is the visual estimate by an expert neuroanatomist; large circle is the estimate by the automated procedure). This indicates that the sections deviated significantly from a coronal stereotaxic plane.

title: cj164-fb-r8c
memo: The FB injection was in the midline part of area 8b, with possible slight invasion of anterior cingulate area 24c. the latter may account for the label in representations of the head in most motor and premotor areas.
case_memo: This animal had 3 good injections in the medial frontal cortex

title: cj74-dy-r17b
memo: DY injection in the caudal part of area 8b. Pattern of label is similar to FB injection suggesting no involvement of cortex caudal to 8b (area 6M).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study on the connections of marmoset caudal prefrontal cortex, focused on subdivisions of area 8.

title: cj801-ctbgr-r8b
memo: The CTB-green injection was centred in the most rostral part of area 6DR, but there was likely invasion of adjacent area 8aD. This injection extended into the subjacent white matter.
case_memo: This animal had 3 effective injections in the frontal cortex. There was also a failed attempt to inject area 11 with CTB-red (track visible in section r6c).

title: cj125x-fe-r17a
memo: FE injection in area 6DR. CARET reconstruction illustrated in Figure 12B of Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol 522:3683–3716).
case_memo: This animal had 2 tracer injections (FE and FR) in the dorsolateral surface of the caudal frontal cortex.

title: cj123-fe-r17b
memo: The FE injection in area 8C appeared in the paper by Burman et al. (2015) as case 4 (Fig. 12).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in subdivisions of the caudal frontal cortex, centred on subdivisions of the premotor cortex.

title: cj100-fr-r17b
memo: FR injection in the dorsal part of area 6DR; previously illustrated as case 4 in Burman et al. J Comp Neurol 522:3683–3716 (2014).
case_memo:
This case was part of a series of experiments on the afferent connections of somatosensory and motor cortex.

Data on frontal lobe connections need to be interpreted with caution as there is a large ischemic damage to areas 8Ad and rostral part of 6DR in the hemisphere ipsilateral to the injections. This is most apparent between sections r11 and r18.

title: cj110-fe-r17b
memo: FE injection in area 6DR. This injection was published as case 5 in Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol. 522:3683–3716). Data illustrated in Figures 10 and 11 of this paper.
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj94-fr-r20b
memo: FR injection in area 6DR. Results unpublished but very similar to those of case 3 (CJ125FE), shown in Burman et al. (J Comp Neurol 522:3683–3716,2014)
case_memo: Animal with multiple injections in the caudal part of the frontal lobe.

title: cj801-fb-r9c
memo: The FB injection was well centred in area 8C, but was relatively large, so invasion of adjacent areas is likely. Labeled neurones were found in multiple subdivisions of visual and posterior parietal cortex as expected from a 8C injection.
case_memo: This animal had 3 effective injections in the frontal cortex. There was also a failed attempt to inject area 11 with CTB-red (track visible in section r6c).

title: cj116-fr-r16a
memo: The FR injection was published as case 1 in the paper by Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol 522:3683–3716).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj215-fb-r14b
memo: The FB injection was centred on the middle layers of the rostral part of anterior cingulate area 24b. Contamination of adjacent areas 8b and 32 by the injection halo was either minimal or absent)
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective tracer injections

title: cj110-fr-r17b
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, ventral, part a
memo: FR injection in area 6Va, published as case 1 in Burman et al. 2015 (J Comp Neurol 523:1222–1247), and presented in Figures 8 and 9 of this paper.
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj100-fe-r17b
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, ventral, part a
memo: FE injection involving area 8C and dorsal part of area 6Va; previously illustrated as case 5 in Burman et al. J Comp Neurol 523:1222–1247 (2015).
case_memo:
This case was part of a series of experiments on the afferent connections of somatosensory and motor cortex.

Data on frontal lobe connections need to be interpreted with caution as there is a large ischemic damage to areas 8Ad and rostral part of 6DR in the hemisphere ipsilateral to the injections. This is most apparent between sections r11 and r18.

title: cj112-fr-r20a
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, ventral, part a
memo: FR injection in area 6aV, published as case 3 in Burman et al. 2015 (J Comp Neurol 523:1222–1247)). CARET reconstruction shown in Figure 10B of this paper.
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj111-fe-r20a
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, ventral, part a
memo: FE injection in area 6Va. This injection was published in Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol 522: 811-843) as an injection at the border between 6Va and the face representation in area 4 (4c). Subsequent reanalysis show that the injection was in fact entirely contained in cytoarchitectural area 6Va.
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj227-fb-r10d
memo: The FB injection was well contained to the midline (anterior cingulate) cortex. It was centred in area 24b, but also invaded area 24c.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but one (CTBg) did not result in long-distance label. There were some problems during the sectioning, resulting in the rostral block not being sectioned exactly in the coronal plane.

title: cj195-ctbgr-r11d
memo: A small injection if CTB-green was placed in areas 24c and 24d. This resulted in few labeled neurones, and inconclusive results.
case_memo: This animal had 3 tracer injections along the midline cortex. Histology suffered from damage to the ventral temporal lobe incurred during tissue processing, and several sections (c20b to r16a) are fragmented and/ or have missing parts in this region. Fortunately there was no evidence of  labeled neurones in the neighbourhood of the damage, or in the fragments preserved, so results are likely not affected by this mishap.

title: cj116-fe-r18a
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, ventral, part a
memo: The FE injection was published as case 2 in the paper by Burman et al. 2015 (J Comp Neurol 523:1222–1247).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj164-ctbgr-r10c
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, medial (supplementary motor) part
memo: CTB (green) injection was restricted to the rostral part of area 6M (supplementary motor). The pattern of label differs somewhat from more caudal injections assigned to area 6M, but lacks the projections from superior temporal cortex that are observed following injections in area 8b.
case_memo: This animal had 3 good injections in the medial frontal cortex

title: cj170-dy-r9d
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, medial (supplementary motor) part
memo: The DY injection was restricted to the medial premotor cortex (area 6M).
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections of tracers in part of the somatosensory and motor complex of areas. The histology presented here uses the cytochrome oxidase stain.

title: cj113-fe-r19a
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, medial (supplementary motor) part
memo: FE injection in area 6M (supplementary motor).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj163-fb-r20a
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, medial (supplementary motor) part
memo: FB injection in area 6M, with the halo slightly invading areas 24c/d.
case_memo:
This animal had 4 injections in the medial frontal lobe: FB and DY in the left hemisphere and CTB (red and green) in the right. The injections reconstructed here are the FB and DY (images were flipped so injections appear on the right, to facilitate comparison with other cars). 

This animal also underwent electrophysiological recordings in extrastriate cortex. This resulted in some herniation and electrode tracks, visible for example in the neighbourhood of section c26b.

title: cj94-fb-r21b
region_name: Area 6 of cortex, medial (supplementary motor) part
memo: FB injection in the caudal part of area 6M (supplementary motor)
case_memo: Animal with multiple injections in the caudal part of the frontal lobe.

title: cj112-fe-r20a
memo: FE injection published as case 7 in Burman et al. 2014  (J Comp Neurol. 522:3683–3716). CARET reconstruction illustrated in Figure 15A of this paper.
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj115-fe-r19b
memo: The FE injection was located in the dorsal part of area 6DC. A computerised reconstruction with expert assessment of histological boundaries was published as case 8 in Burman et al. (2014; J Comp Neurol 522:3683–3716).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj123-fr-r21a
memo: The FR injection in area 6DC appeared in the paper by Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol 522:3683–3716) as case 9 (Fig. 9C)
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in subdivisions of the caudal frontal cortex, centred on subdivisions of the premotor cortex.

title: cj111-fr-r21b
memo: FR injection near the dorsal limit of area 6DC. This injection site consisted of 3 needle tracks with tracer deposited along each. This case was presented as case 10 in Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol. 522:3683–3716), with manual reconstruction of data appearing in Figures 13 and 14.
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj115-fr-r20b
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, part c (primary motor)
memo: The FR injection was placed in the head representation of  primary motor cortex (cytoarchitectural area 4c). A computerised reconstruction incorporating expert-assessed area borders was published as case 9 in the study by Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol 522: 811–843).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj167-ctbgr-r12a
memo: An elongated injection of CTBgreen was placed along the midline, involving primarily area 24d but with invasion of adjacent area 24c and  possibly the most medial part of the primary motor cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections in the motor/ premotor complex of areas, all including the midline. Histology was done using a neuron-specific (NeuN) staining instead of Nissl. The results were rather pleasing.

title: cj167-fb-r13b
memo: The FB injection was very small, and restricted to a subdivision of the medial motor cortex (area 24d)
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections in the motor/ premotor complex of areas, all including the midline. Histology was done using a neuron-specific (NeuN) staining instead of Nissl. The results were rather pleasing.

title: cj195-fb-r15a
memo: The FB injection involved the most medial part of the primary motor cortex (cytoarchitectural area 4a/b of Burman et al. 2008 J Comp Neurol 506: 860-876), but crossed significantly into area 24d of the cingulate motor cortex. The pattern of label indicates that the injection primarily involved representations of the hindlimb and trunk. Involvement of area 24d is confirmed by the presence of label in prefrontal cortex (with emphasis on area 8aD; see also Bakola et al. Cereb Cortex 2021; https://doi.org/10.1093/cercor/bhab193).
case_memo: This animal had 3 tracer injections along the midline cortex. Histology suffered from damage to the ventral temporal lobe incurred during tissue processing, and several sections (c20b to r16a) are fragmented and/ or have missing parts in this region. Fortunately there was no evidence of  labeled neurones in the neighbourhood of the damage, or in the fragments preserved, so results are likely not affected by this mishap.

title: cj167-fr-r14c
memo: The FR injection was very restricted, and centred in area 24d. It may have extended into adjacent areas 23 and the medial part of the primary motor cortex, but this appears minimal.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections in the motor/ premotor complex of areas, all including the midline. Histology was done using a neuron-specific (NeuN) staining instead of Nissl. The results were rather pleasing.

title: cj209-dy-r22a
memo: The DY injection was well centred in rostral auditory belt area RTL, with possible minimal invasion of core area RT and the superior temporal rostral auditory association cortex (STR). The injection included most layers but seems to avoid layer 6.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. The CTB green injection invaded the white matter and possibly one of the small islands near the caudal end of the caudate nucleus.

title: cj102x-dy-r12b
memo: This animal had a single effective injection (DY) in the representation of the face/ oral structures of primary somatosensory cortex. The injection site most likely crossed  from area 3b to area 1/2.
case_memo: This case yielded a single useful injection (DY). Other injections did not result in transport.

title: cj114-fe-r25a
memo: A small FE injection was located in the primary somatosensory cortex (area 3b), mainly in the supra granular layers.
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj187-ctbgr-r12c
memo: The CTBgreen injection was placed on the lateral surface of the rostral temporal lobe, crossing from parts of the lateral belt (area RTL) into the rostral parabelt. This injection resulted in fewer labeled neurones, in comparison with CTBred, resulting in sparser label patterns. This may be explainable by the fact that this injection followed a trajectory largely parallel to layer 4, and did not involve infra granular layers. Nonetheless, the long-range extrinsic connections to these injections revealed by these two injections originated in overlapping regions  (e.g. in the medial part of frontopolar area 10).
case_memo: This case had 3 effective injections. A fourth injection (DY) was attempted, but led to no labeled cells due to equipment malfunction.

title: cj78-dy-r28b
memo: DY injection in area 3a crossing into caudal M1 (case 8 in Burman et al. 2014).
case_memo: This animal was part of a study aimed at the connections of the primary motor area (Burman et al. 2014; J Comp Neurol 522:811–843). Thalamic label show in Figure 2 of this paper.

title: cj213-ctbgr-r33a
memo: The CTBgr injection was contained in area 3a, most likely in the region representing the forelimb musculature.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections, including 2 in the ventrolateral prefrontal cortex and 2 in somatomotor cortex

title: w6hl-ctbgr-c46b
memo: The CTBgr injection was placed entirely within the primary somatosensory area (3b), most likely near the the face/ digits representation border.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. It received 4 tracer injections in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere after 20 months from the lesion creation. Images of sections are flipped left-right to facilitate comparison with other cases. 
Other results from this case have been published (Atapour et al. 2021 Brain Struct Funct 226:2763-2775; 2022 Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 119(4):e2117137119).

title: cj170-fb-r15d
memo: The FB injection was small and restricted to somatosensory area 3a.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections of tracers in part of the somatosensory and motor complex of areas. The histology presented here uses the cytochrome oxidase stain.

title: cj170-ctbr-r15d
memo: The CTB-red injection in this case was restricted to the primary somatosensory cortex (area 3b) in the forelimb representation.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections of tracers in part of the somatosensory and motor complex of areas. The histology presented here uses the cytochrome oxidase stain.

title: cj173-fb-r18a
memo: The FB injection was large, and included parts of two subdivisions of somatosensory cortex (areas 3b and 1/2).
case_memo:
This animal had 4 effective injections in areas involved in somatic sensation and motor control. The histological sections presented are stained for cytochrome oxidase. 
There was loss of tissue in the ventral temporal cortex due to an accident during sectioning. The sections illustrated show "padding" of this part of the brain (digital manipulation), which was necessary to enable registration to template. Users are advised to ignore the histology in this part of the brain.

title: cj209-fb-c43b
memo: The FB injection was centred in somatosensory area 1/2, but crossed the cytoarchitectural border with the rostral part of PE. This resulted in a pattern of label that included most somatosensory and motor areas. All cortical layers were included.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. The CTB green injection invaded the white matter and possibly one of the small islands near the caudal end of the caudate nucleus.

title: cj180-fb-r13b
memo: The FB injection was large, and included multiple areas of the anterior auditory cortex. It was centred in area RT, and included parts of RTL, RTM and AL
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in the temporal lobe.

title: cj122-dy-r28b
memo: DY injection centred in the rostrotemporal auditory area (AuRT), but with significant involvement of the anterolateral belt area (AuAL).
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in temporal cortex.

title: cj114-fr-r25a
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, parts a and b (primary motor)
memo: The FR injection was assessed as being in the forelimb representation of the primary motor cortex (cytoarchitectural area 4ab). A computerised reconstruction with expert delineation of areal bounraries was published as case 6 in the paper by Burman et al. (J Comp Neurol 522:811–843, 2014).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj213-fb-r28a
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, parts a and b (primary motor)
memo: The FB injection was centred in the primary motor cortex (cytoarchitectural field 4ab), but crossed into area 3a. The injection most likely closed from the representation of the hands to that of the head musculature.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections, including 2 in the ventrolateral prefrontal cortex and 2 in somatomotor cortex

title: cj78-fe-r26b
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, parts a and b (primary motor)
memo: FE injection in the intermediate part of M1 (putative forelimb representation; case 7 in Burman et al. 2014). CARET reconstruction illustrated in Figure 11 of the paper.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study aimed at the connections of the primary motor area (Burman et al. 2014; J Comp Neurol 522:811–843). Thalamic label show in Figure 2 of this paper.

title: cj173-dy-r14c
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, parts a and b (primary motor)
memo: The DY injection was small and restricted to the supra granular layers of primary motor cortex (cytoarchitectural area 4a/b).
case_memo:
This animal had 4 effective injections in areas involved in somatic sensation and motor control. The histological sections presented are stained for cytochrome oxidase. 
There was loss of tissue in the ventral temporal cortex due to an accident during sectioning. The sections illustrated show "padding" of this part of the brain (digital manipulation), which was necessary to enable registration to template. Users are advised to ignore the histology in this part of the brain.

title: cj113-fr-r26a
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, parts a and b (primary motor)
memo: FR injection in the medial part of area 4 (primary motor). CARET reconstruction illustrated in Figure 10A of Burman et al. 2014 (J Comp Neurol 522:811–843).
case_memo: This animal had 2 injections (FR and FE) in somatosensory/ motor cortex.

title: cj78-fb-r28b
region_name: Area 4 of cortex, parts a and b (primary motor)
memo: FB injection in caudal medial M1 (case 4 in Burman et al. 2014). CARET reconstruction illustrated in Figure 8 of the paper.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study aimed at the connections of the primary motor area (Burman et al. 2014; J Comp Neurol 522:811–843). Thalamic label show in Figure 2 of this paper.

title: cj167-dy-r15d
memo: The DY injection was an elongated deposit of tracer along the midline, centred in area 23c, but invading the medial end of area 3a, and the most rostral part of area 23b.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections in the motor/ premotor complex of areas, all including the midline. Histology was done using a neuron-specific (NeuN) staining instead of Nissl. The results were rather pleasing.

title: cj122-fr-r33a
memo: FR injection largely restricted to the caudal parabelt area (AuCPB), with possible minor involvement of anterolateral belt.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in temporal cortex.

title: cj122-fb-r37b
region_name: Temporo-parieto-occipital association area (superior temporal polysensory cortex)
memo: A large FB injection created by insertion of a crystal involved primarily polysensory temporal association areas (TPO, PGa/ IPa), with the centre being located in area TPO (superior temporal polysensory area). The rostral limit of the injection may have invaded the caudal part of the auditory parabelt.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in temporal cortex.

title: cj122-fe-r38b
region_name: Temporo-parieto-occipital association area (superior temporal polysensory cortex)
memo: The FE injection was centred in the caudal most part of area TPO, but is likely to have involved the border with visual areas MST and FST (note presence of label in the peripheral representations of extra striate areas e.g. V2, V3, V4).
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in temporal cortex.

title: cj802-ctbr-r16c
memo: The CTB-red injection was restricted to the supragranular layers of the external segment of somatosensory area S2 (S2E)
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. There was some loss of ventral temporal lobe tissue due to an accident during histological processing, which is apparent between sections r11b and r21b. However, analysis of the detached segment of cortex showed few if any labeled neurones are likely to have been missed in the analysis of connections.

title: cj170-ctbgr-r17a
memo: The CTB-green injection was centred in the second somatosensory area (S2), bit appears to have extended to adjacent posterior parietal area PF
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections of tracers in part of the somatosensory and motor complex of areas. The histology presented here uses the cytochrome oxidase stain.

title: w6hl-ctbr-c42b
memo: The CTBr injection was contained in the lateral part of the primary auditory area (A1)
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. It received 4 tracer injections in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere after 20 months from the lesion creation. Images of sections are flipped left-right to facilitate comparison with other cases. 
Other results from this case have been published (Atapour et al. 2021 Brain Struct Funct 226:2763-2775; 2022 Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 119(4):e2117137119).

title: cj187-ctbr-r16d
memo: The CTBred injection was in the lateral part of the primary auditory area (A1). It likely involved all cortical layers. Although most labeled neurones were located in other auditory areas, this case also showed a complex pattern of label, including connections with the cingulate, parahippocampal and frontal regions. In this respect, its results contrast with those revealed by a smaller injection (case CJ75-FR). There was no evidence of involvement of white matter, and the only possible invasion of adjacent areas would be the lateral belt, near layers 5/6 (section r17b).
case_memo: This case had 3 effective injections. A fourth injection (DY) was attempted, but led to no labeled cells due to equipment malfunction.

title: cj75x-fr-r34b
memo: FR injection restricted to primary auditory area (A1).
case_memo: Case with 2 good injections (FR and DY). There was ischemic damage to the dorsal surface.

title: cj77-dy-c39b
memo: The small DY injection was concentrated in the supra granular layers of cytoarchitectural area PF (with likely minor involvement of PFG). In comparison with other injections in posterior parietal cortex, this one labeled a larger proportion of neurones in somatosensory and motor areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in posterior parietal cortex but the FE injection was ineffective.

title: cj64-fr-c23a
memo: FR was a small injection in the caudal auditory belt (area CM). Resulted primarily in label in other auditory areas. Scattered label in frontal cortex (centered in area 8aV), caudal insular areas, and the S2 complex.
case_memo: This case received 4 injections in the caudal temporal lobe. The DY injection (visible in section r15a) was not processed due to some loss of label near the junction of rostral and caudal blocks.

title: cj181nm-ctbgr-c21c
memo: The CTB-green injection was centred in the caudomedial auditory area (CM), but seems to have crossed into the rostral part of area MST (according to Paxinos et al. 2012). A more recent reanalysis (Majka et al. 2019; Brain Struct Funct 224:111-131.) indicates that this part of "MST" is likely to correspond to the caudal part of the superior temporal polysensory area (TPOC) of the macaque.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj209-ctbgr-c41b
memo: The CTB-green injection was centred in the caudomedial auditory area (CM). However it resulted in an extensive pattern of label across the infragranular layers of the cortex, which suggests that the tracer deposit included the white matter and, possibly, the subjacent caudate nucleus. Connections in this case needs to be interpreted carefully.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. The CTB green injection invaded the white matter and possibly one of the small islands near the caudal end of the caudate nucleus.

title: cj181-ctbgr-c21c
memo: The CTB-green injection was centred in the caudomedial auditory area (CM), but seems to have crossed into the rostral part of visual area MST. This region may correspond to the caudal part of the superior temporal polysensry area (TPOC) according to Majka et al. 2019 (Brain Struct Funct 224: 111-131).
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj64-fe-c29a
memo: FE was a small injection in the auditory cortex (lateral belt, centered in area ML). Resulted primarily in local label in auditory and caudal insular areas.
case_memo: This case received 4 injections in the caudal temporal lobe. The DY injection (visible in section r15a) was not processed due to some loss of label near the junction of rostral and caudal blocks.

title: cj802-ctbgr-r17d
memo: the CTB-green injection was placed in lateral auditory cortex, involving parts of belt (primarily area ML) and caudal parabelt areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. There was some loss of ventral temporal lobe tissue due to an accident during histological processing, which is apparent between sections r11b and r21b. However, analysis of the detached segment of cortex showed few if any labeled neurones are likely to have been missed in the analysis of connections.

title: cj180-ctbgr-r17d
memo: Injection of CTB-green was centred in the ventral auditory cortex, probably including parts of various areas (CL, ML, and caudal parabelt)
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in the temporal lobe.

title: cj182-ctbr-r18d
region_name: Parietal areas PGa and IPa (fundus of superior temporal ventral area)
memo: The CTB-red injection was restricted to cytoarchitectural fields IPa/PGa (also known as FSTv).
case_memo: This animal had 3 effective injections in the rostral visual cortex and superior temporal region.

title: cj204r-dy-c19d
memo: The DY injection was located primarily in the rostral part of area PFG, but likely crossed into the supra granular layers of area PF. The pattern of label was in some respects very similar to that revealed by injections in area AIP in other animals, which may suggest that this area extends more rostrally than presently recognised, forming a strip that separates PFG and PF from PE at rostral levels.

title: cj76-fe-c39b
memo: FE injection was small, and restricted to cytoarchitectural area PFG. Involvement of the infragranular layers was incomplete.
case_memo: This case had 4 injections in the posterior parietal cortex. Only 1 section in 800 µm is used as the basis of the analysis shown here as the alternate series could not be plotted consistently due to histology artefacts in the fluorescence series.

title: cj76-dy-c36b
memo: DY injection was a large deposit (crystal) inserted in area PFG. The edges of the injection most likely invaded the anterior intraparietal area (AIP).
case_memo: This case had 4 injections in the posterior parietal cortex. Only 1 section in 800 µm is used as the basis of the analysis shown here as the alternate series could not be plotted consistently due to histology artefacts in the fluorescence series.

title: cj205-ctbgr-c38a
memo: The CTB-green injection straddled the border between posterior parietal areas PFG and PG. the pattern of label was extensive, and seems to combine features observed in injections in both of these areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj173-ctbr-r19d
memo: The CTB red injection was near the rostral border of parietal area PE. Histology indicates that there was likely invasion of somatosensory area 1/2.
case_memo:
This animal had 4 effective injections in areas involved in somatic sensation and motor control. The histological sections presented are stained for cytochrome oxidase. 
There was loss of tissue in the ventral temporal cortex due to an accident during sectioning. The sections illustrated show "padding" of this part of the brain (digital manipulation), which was necessary to enable registration to template. Users are advised to ignore the histology in this part of the brain.

title: cj183-fb-c19c
region_name: Medial superior temporal area of cortex
memo: The FB injection was confined to the boundaries of area MST, defined according to the Paxinos et al. (2012) stereotaxic atlas. Correspondingly, there was label in the representation of the far periphery of the visual field in most visual areas, in a agreement with Palmer and Rosa (Eur J Neurosci 24(8):2389-2405, 2006). However, note that this injection also led to label in many auditory cortex areas. This may reflect the need to subdivide MST into two areas, with the most rostral subdivision corresponding to polysensory area TPOc of the macaque (for discussion see Majka et al. Brain Struct Funct 224(1):111-131, 2019).
case_memo: This case had 4 effective injections.

title: cj189nm-fb-c19d
memo: Fast Blue was injected in the most lateral part of posterior parietal area PE, with possible involvement of the anterior intraparietal area (AIP).
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj192-dy-c20a
region_name: Medial superior temporal area of cortex
memo: DY was injected in the medial superior temporal area of Paxinos et al. (2012). Involvement of adjacent areas was minimal. Note however that according to Majka et al. (Brain Struct Funct 224:111-131, 2019) this cytoarchitectural area is likely to include 2 functional fields: MST proper and the caudal subdivision of poly sensory area TPO (TPOc). The complex pattern of label, involving both the far peripheral representations of visual areas (e.g. V1-V4, MT, DM) and polysensory and auditory areas is compatible with this hypothesis.
case_memo:
This animal had 4 tracer injections, of which 3 (DY, FB and CTB-red) were restricted to cortex, and 1 (CTB-green) included white matter. The same animal was also used to obtain electrophysiological recordings in a non-recovery experiment following the survival time required by the tracers; electrode tracks are visible in several sections. 
Some damage to the frontal lobe tissue occurred during extraction of the brain from the skull post-perfusion; this is evident between sections r4a-r5d (areas 12/ 47 and 8aV), and r5d-r8b (area 8b). This may have affected cell counts in these areas.

title: cj189-fb-c19d
memo: Fast Blue was injected in the most lateral part of posterior parietal area PE, with possible involvement of the anterior intraparietal area (AIP).
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: w6hl-dy-c35a
region_name: Medial superior temporal area of cortex
memo: The DY injection was contained in the lateral part of the dial superior temporal (MST) area, leading to  a pattern of label that includes representations of the far periphery of the visual field across all visual areas.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. It received 4 tracer injections in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere after 20 months from the lesion creation. Images of sections are flipped left-right to facilitate comparison with other cases. 
Other results from this case have been published (Atapour et al. 2021 Brain Struct Funct 226:2763-2775; 2022 Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 119(4):e2117137119).

title: cj200r-dy-c19d
memo: The DY injection was restricted to posterior parietal area PE, approximately in the centre of this area.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but only 3 were restricted to cortex.

title: cj209-ctbr-c37a
memo: The CTB-red injection was well centred in parietal area PE, with minimal to no invasion of the white matter. All cortical layers were included.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. The CTB green injection invaded the white matter and possibly one of the small islands near the caudal end of the caudate nucleus.

title: cj183-ctbr-c18b
memo: The CTB-red injection was also located in the posterior parietal cortex, this time in the caudal most part of cytoarchitectural area PE. This region of the marmoset cortex is admittedly still not mapped in detail, so homologies with the macaque are at the moment tentative, and this information may evolve, including in light of the present connectional results.
case_memo: This case had 4 effective injections.

title: w6bl-fe-c32b
region_name: Medial superior temporal area of cortex
memo: The FE injection crossed from the dorsal border of area MT into area MST, leading to label in the representations of the far peripheral visual field in extra striate areas and V1.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, which encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. The lesion was created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal.
After reaching adulthood this animal received 2 injections (FE and FR) in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere. It also received electrophysiological recordings in a terminal session (Yu et al. 2013, J Neurosci 33:12479 –12489)

title: cj51-dy-c20b
region_name: Medial superior temporal area of cortex
memo: DY injection centred  on the dorsal part of area MST. Label included peripheral representations of most visual areas.
case_memo: Likely small involvement of inferior parietal area PG as suggested by label in posterior cingulate and orbitofrontal areas.

title: cj200r-ctbgr-c15d
memo: The CTB-green injection was centred on the fibre bundles originating from the splenium of the corpus callosum, but also involved parts of the hippocampus formation. It led to a complex pattern of label including cells that originate interhemispheric connections along the V1/ V2 border.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but only 3 were restricted to cortex.

title: cj192-ctbgr-c15a
memo: CTB-green was injected deep in the calcarine sulcus, involving primarily area 29 (a-c), but leaked in the adjacent white matter. This led to a complex pattern of label, which emphasised medial temporal (parahippocampal, entorhinal), retrosplenial, cingulate and pericallosal cortex, as well as the foveal representations of various visual areas. Label in the hippocampal formation (not shown) was also substantial. The sparser label may be attributed to passing fibres, so interpretation needs to be made with caution.
case_memo:
This animal had 4 tracer injections, of which 3 (DY, FB and CTB-red) were restricted to cortex, and 1 (CTB-green) included white matter. The same animal was also used to obtain electrophysiological recordings in a non-recovery experiment following the survival time required by the tracers; electrode tracks are visible in several sections. 
Some damage to the frontal lobe tissue occurred during extraction of the brain from the skull post-perfusion; this is evident between sections r4a-r5d (areas 12/ 47 and 8aV), and r5d-r8b (area 8b). This may have affected cell counts in these areas.

title: cj146l-dy-r41a
memo: The DY injection was centred in area 23b, but reached further ventrally into area 23a.
case_memo:
This animal had different injections in  the two hemispheres (FB in right, DY and FR in left). Because the reconstruction of each hemisphere is run separately, this appears here as two cases (CJ146R and CJ146L). Sections from left hemisphere have been flipped horizontally to preserve the common format of all cases and facilitate comparisons.

An electrophysiological experiment using an "Utah" multilectrode array was also conducted. Tracks can be observed (see e.g. sections r46a/ b).

We experienced problems during sectioning of the caudal block, so histology at some caudal levels is suboptimal, in particular with tears in the white matter.

title: cj204r-ctbr-c18d
memo: The CTB red injection was centered in the rostral part of area 23a, with some likely involvement of areas 23b and 30. The pattern of label was distinct from that found in more caudal injections involving this area, particularly with respect to connections arising from the ventral temporal cortex (e.g areas TH and entorhinal, which was much more marked.

title: cj802-dy-r20d
memo: The DY injection was placed in the anterior intraparietal area (AIP), but may have invaded a more lateral area (cytoarchitectural area PFG) to a small extent.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. There was some loss of ventral temporal lobe tissue due to an accident during histological processing, which is apparent between sections r11b and r21b. However, analysis of the detached segment of cortex showed few if any labeled neurones are likely to have been missed in the analysis of connections.

title: cj146-fb-r45a
memo: The FB injection was centred in area 23b, but likely invaded area 31.
case_memo:
This animal had different injections in  the two hemispheres (FB in right, DY and FR in left). Because the reconstruction of each hemisphere is run separately, this appears here as two cases (CJ146R and CJ146L). Sections from left hemisphere have been flipped horizontally to preserve the common format of all cases and facilitate comparisons.

An electrophysiological experiment using an "Utah" multilectrode array was also conducted. Tracks can be observed (see e.g. sections r46a/ b).

We experienced problems during sectioning of the caudal block, so histology at some caudal levels is suboptimal, in particular with tears in the white matter.

title: cj173-ctbgr-r22d
memo: The CTB-green injection was located in the rostral part of the posterior parietal cortex, centred in the anterior intraparietal area (AIP).
case_memo:
This animal had 4 effective injections in areas involved in somatic sensation and motor control. The histological sections presented are stained for cytochrome oxidase. 
There was loss of tissue in the ventral temporal cortex due to an accident during sectioning. The sections illustrated show "padding" of this part of the brain (digital manipulation), which was necessary to enable registration to template. Users are advised to ignore the histology in this part of the brain.

title: cj189nm-ctbgr-c17d
memo: CTB-green was injected in medial posterior parietal area 31.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj189-ctbgr-c17d
memo: CTB-green was injected in medial posterior parietal area 31.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj195-dy-c18a
memo: The DY injection was placed in the posterior cingulate cortex (including parts of areas 23a and 23b). It was a clean injection with no leakage of tracer up the needle track. The results are consistent with those of other injections in the same region (e.g. CJ153-FR).
case_memo: This animal had 3 tracer injections along the midline cortex. Histology suffered from damage to the ventral temporal lobe incurred during tissue processing, and several sections (c20b to r16a) are fragmented and/ or have missing parts in this region. Fortunately there was no evidence of  labeled neurones in the neighbourhood of the damage, or in the fragments preserved, so results are likely not affected by this mishap.

title: cj153x-fr-c17d
memo: The FR injection was very successful in resulting in a restricted stein posterior cingulate cortex, largely contained in area 23b.
case_memo: This animal had injections in both hemispheres but results were of unequal quality.

title: cj84-fe-c17a
memo: FE injection was very small, restricted to supragranular layers of area 23a (near caudal end).
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj146l-fr-r49a
memo: The FR injection was located in the infragranular layers of  the midline cortex. It was centred in area 23a but probably included portions of adjacent areas. Plots of this injection are only available for sections every 800 µm.

title: cj80-fb-c36a
memo: The FB injection was centred in area 23b, but the halo invaded cortex located more dorsally along the midline (probably area 31).
case_memo: This animal had injections directed to the posterior cingulate region. The right hemisphere (on the left of the images) had damage incurred during the surgery for injection but the injected hemisphere had no damage.

title: cj80-fr-c35a
memo: The FR injection was quite small, and straddled the border between cytoarchitectural areas 23a and 23b. Unlike more rostral injections in area 23, this case revealed substantial connections with visual areas, suggesting that area 23 has rostrocaudal subdivisions.
case_memo: This animal had injections directed to the posterior cingulate region. The right hemisphere (on the left of the images) had damage incurred during the surgery for injection but the injected hemisphere had no damage.

title: cj180-ctbr-r16c
memo: The CTB-red injection was located in the inferior temporal cortex. Preliminary analysis suggests a location in cytoarchitectural area TE3, but invasion of adjacent polysensory cortex is possible.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in the temporal lobe.

title: cj207-ctbgr-c42a
memo: The CTB-green injection included the supragranular layers of cytoarchitectural area PGa/IPa, and the dorsal most part of cytoarchitectural area TE3.
case_memo: This animal received 4 tracer injections, but the DY injection invaded the white matter extensively and has not been analysed. The DY injection site is visible in section c30a.

title: cj180-dy-r20a
memo: The DY injection was placed in the dorsal part of cytoarchitectural area TE3,.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in the temporal lobe.

title: w6dl-dy-c36b
memo: The DY injection was in the centre of inferior temporal area TE3.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the left hemisphere, which encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. The lesion was created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal.
After reaching adulthood this animal received 2 injections (FB and DY) in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere. It also received FE and FR injections in the right (non-lesioned) hemisphere.

title: cj203nm-dy-c18c
memo: The DY injection was well restricted to area PG, and involved most layers. The halo may have entered the rostral part of area PFG, but given the subtle nature of the cytoarchitectural transition this is uncertain. This injection was more effective than most others in PG, leading to an extensive pattern of label involving association areas in frontal, parietal, ventral temporal and cingulate cortex.
case_memo: This animal received 4 injections, but only two satisfied the inclusion criteria: a DY injection in posterior parietal area PG, and a CTB-red injection in the retrosplenial cortex (area 23V).

title: cj802-fb-r21b
memo: The FB injection involved the junction of various parietal areas. the bulk of the injection was located in cytoarchitectural area PG, but parts of it involved caudal (PG, MST) and possibly rostral (TPt) areas, resulting in a complex pattern of label.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections. There was some loss of ventral temporal lobe tissue due to an accident during histological processing, which is apparent between sections r11b and r21b. However, analysis of the detached segment of cortex showed few if any labeled neurones are likely to have been missed in the analysis of connections.

title: cj203-dy-c18c

title: w6f-ctbgr-c32a
memo: The injection of CTB-green was in parietal area PG, and encompassed all layers with m animal to no involvement of white matter or the adjacent area (LIP)
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, created at the age of 38 days postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. It received 4 tracer injections in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere after 16 months from the lesion creation. Images of sections are flipped left-right to facilitate comparison with other cases. 
Other results from this case have been published (Atapour et al. 2021 Brain Struct Funct 226:2763-2775; 2022 Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 119(4):e2117137119).

title: cj76-fr-c30b
memo: FR injection was small, and restricted to cytoarchitectural area PG
case_memo: This case had 4 injections in the posterior parietal cortex. Only 1 section in 800 µm is used as the basis of the analysis shown here as the alternate series could not be plotted consistently due to histology artefacts in the fluorescence series.

title: cj55-dy-c24b
memo: A large DY injection consisting of multiple crystals was centred in parietal area PG, with likely involvement of visual area MST. The patter of label was complex, being very similar to that revealed by the FB injection, but including a wider variety of prefrontal and orbitofrontal areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the posterior parietal region.

title: cj77-fr-c31b
memo: FR was a small injection in cytoarchitectural area PG, which led to labeling of relatively few neurones.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in posterior parietal cortex but the FE injection was ineffective.

title: cj50-dy-c26b
memo: DY Injection in the inferior parietal cortex, near the border between cytoarchitectural areas PG and Opt.
case_memo: Animal with injections in the ventral part of the occipitoparietal transition cortex.

title: w6al-dy-c32a

case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, which encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. The lesion was created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal.

title: w2b-fe-c36a
memo: The FR injection was well contained within the representation of peripheral vision in area V5 (MT). The injection volume was small so relatively few labeled neurons were observed.
case_memo: This animal had a unilateral left hemisphere V1 lesion on 6/10/2009, at 2 weeks postnatal. The injections were placed approximately 1 year later, followed by an acute electrophysiology session on 27/10/10. Results of recordings from area MT were presented in Yu et al. 2013 (J Neurosci 33:12479 –12489)

title: cj56-fr-c24a
memo: FR injection in the far peripheral representation of area MT (monocular crescent). Manual reconstruction illustrated in Figure 4 of Palmer and Rosa  2006 (Eur J Neurosci 24: 2389–2405).
case_memo: Animal with injections in the caudal temporal lobe, as part of a study of connections of area MT. The process of registration to the template in this case employed an early version of the computational pipeline, which did not use area label maps as constraints; hence, caution is advised in interpreting fine details with reference to proposed area boundaries. also noticeable are histological artefacts which led to damage to the Nissl stained sections in the caudal block.

title: w6p-dy-c32b
memo: The DY injection was in the representation of the far periphery of the visual field, and appeared to be restricted to area MT.
case_memo: This animal had a large V1 lesion placed in the left hemisphere at the age of 5 weeks postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. Two tracer injections (FB and DY) were placed on the left (lesioned) hemisphere after 24  months (723 days) of recovery. Images of the sections are flipped left-right in order to facilitate comparison with other cases.

title: w6e-fb-c33b
memo: The FB injection was located in the peripheral upper quadrant representation of area MT. The halo may have slightly invaded the medial superior temporal area (MST), having just  touched the MT?MST border.
case_memo: This animal had a large V1 lesion created at 6 week's of age, which destroyed the central representation and the causal part of the calcarine sulcus. It also had electrophysiological recordings in MT and thalamus (primarily in and around the lateral geniculate nucleus) as reported in Yu et al. 2018 (J. Neurosci.38(16):3955–3970), as evidence by the multiple electrode tracks visible in the sections. The total survival time post-lesion was 2 years and 9 months. Two other injections are not reported: fluororuby (invaded the white matter) and fluoroemerald (not effective).

title: cj200r-fb-c17d
memo: The FB injection was aimed at the peripheral visual field representation of area MT (V5), but invaded the medial superior temporal area (MST) ventrally. It led to a pattern of label which is likely to represent the combined afferents of these areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but only 3 were restricted to cortex.

title: w6jl-fr-c32b

title: cj56nm-dy-c20b

title: cj185-dy-c17d
region_name: Visual area 4, transitional part (middle temporal crescent)
memo: The diamindino yellow injection appears to have been largely restricted to area V4T. title: cj192-fb-c17d

case_memo:
This animal had 4 tracer injections, of which 3 (DY, FB and CTB-red) were restricted to cortex, and 1 (CTB-green) included white matter. The same animal was also used to obtain electrophysiological recordings in a non-recovery experiment following the survival time required by the tracers; electrode tracks are visible in several sections. 
Some damage to the frontal lobe tissue occurred during extraction of the brain from the skull post-perfusion; this is evident between sections r4a-r5d (areas 12/ 47 and 8aV), and r5d-r8b (area 8b). This may have affected cell counts in these areas.

title: cj200r-ctbr-c17c
