title: cj52x-dy-c17a
memo: DY injection in superior parietal cortex. Registration to the Paxinos et al. (2012) atlas leads to assignment to cytoarchitectural area PEc. Note however label in peripheral representations of visual areas (MT, DM, V2, MST) and restricted distribution of label in frontal cortex (primarily in areas 8aV and 6DR). This pattern is inconsistent with the connections of PEc in the macaque. It may suggest that the areal boundaries may be incorrect in this region of the marmoset atlas.
case_memo:
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

This case underwent a microsimulation experiment, so electrode tracks can be seen within and around the premotor areas.

Quality of Nissl stain is poor in some frontal sections, which led to suboptimal registration to the template in the anterior temporal cortex. In particular, parcellation in sections r10a and r10b was partially removed as the low quality of staining in these regions precluded accurate registration. However, this has not affected assignment of neurons to areas since there were no labelled cells in the anterior temporal cortex.

title: w6jl-fb-c29a
region_name: Visual area 4, transitional part (middle temporal crescent)
memo: The FB injection was centred in the ventral (upper quadrant representation) of area V4T. However, given its large volume, it most likely invaded the upper vertical meridian representation of area MT and area FST.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, placed at the age of 6 weeks postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. 
The animal received 4 tracer injections (FB, DY, FR and CTB-green) in the left (lesioned) hemisphere after 23 months survival from the lesion. Images of sections are flipped left-right to facilitate comparison with other cases.
Other results from this case have been published (Atapour et al. 2021 Brain Struct Funct 226:2763-2775; 2022 Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 119(4):e2117137119).

title: cj183-ctbgr-c14d
region_name: Visual area 4, transitional part (middle temporal crescent)
memo: The CTB-green injection was contained within the central visual field representation of area V4T, leading to retinotopically matching labeled cells in other visual areas (e.g. V1, V2).
case_memo: This case had 4 effective injections.

title: w6bl-fr-c27b
region_name: Visual area 4, transitional part (middle temporal crescent)
memo: The FR injection was centred in the dorsal part of area V4T, leading to label in the peripheral lower quadrant representation in many extra striate areas.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, which encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. The lesion was created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal.
After reaching adulthood this animal received 2 injections (FE and FR) in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere. It also received electrophysiological recordings in a terminal session (Yu et al. 2013, J Neurosci 33:12479 –12489)

title: cj76-fb-c27b
memo: FB injection straddled the border between the lateral intraparietal area (LIP) and area OPt. The centre of mass was assessed to be in LIP.
case_memo: This case had 4 injections in the posterior parietal cortex. Only 1 section in 800 µm is used as the basis of the analysis shown here as the alternate series could not be plotted consistently due to histology artefacts in the fluorescence series.

title: cj210-fb-c27b
memo: The FB injection was large, and centred on the causal part of the lateral intraparietal area (LIP), with likely invasion of the medial intraparietal area (MIP), and (possibly) a small invasion of area V3a.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but the DY injection was not plotted given extensive track left in the white matter (visible in section c27b).

title: cj55-fb-c22a
memo: A large FB injection was placed at the junction between visual cortex (area MST) and posterior parietal cortex (Opt/ PG). The resulting pattern on label was complex, including peripheral representations in visual cortex (V2, V3, V4, DM, MT) and various association areas in caudomedial, parahippocampal, polysensory (PGa/ IPa), prefrontal (area 12) and posterior parietal regions.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the posterior parietal region.

title: cj205-fb-c31b
memo: The FB injection was in medial parietal/ precuneate cortex, centred in area PGM but with some inclusion of adjacent area 23b. There was no evidence of leakage of tracer up the track.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: w6f-ctbr-c27b
memo: The injection of CTB-red encompassed all layers of cortex. It was centred in the medial intraparietal area (MIP) but likely invaded the ventral intraparieital area (VIP), particularly in the infragranular layers of cortex.
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the injected hemisphere, created at the age of 38 days postnatal. The lesion encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. It received 4 tracer injections in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere after 16 months from the lesion creation. Images of sections are flipped left-right to facilitate comparison with other cases. 
Other results from this case have been published (Atapour et al. 2021 Brain Struct Funct 226:2763-2775; 2022 Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 119(4):e2117137119).

title: cj210-ctbr-c30a
memo: The CTB-red injection crossed from area V6a into medial parietal area PGM.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but the DY injection was not plotted given extensive track left in the white matter (visible in section c27b).

title: cj185-fb-c15c
memo: The Fast Blue injection was largely restricted to the medial intraparietal area (MIP), with possible minor involvement of the ventral intraperietal area (VIP) at rostral levels.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections, but only 3 are presented since a CTB-green injection in peripheral V1 revealed substantial white matter leakage, which led to labeled infra granular neurones in the central representations of various visual areas.

title: cj207-ctbr-c30b
memo: The CTB-red injection was contained within the limits of the medial intraparietal area (MIP) according to the criteria proposed by Paxinos et al. (2012).
case_memo: This animal received 4 tracer injections, but the DY injection invaded the white matter extensively and has not been analysed. The DY injection site is visible in section c30a.

title: cj214-ctbgr-c31b
memo: The CTBgr injection was centred in the Medial Intraparietal area (MIP, with possible invasion of the adjacent Ventral Intraparietal area (VIP). It included all layers of cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 4 good injections, 2 in prefrontal cortex (CTBr and DY), 1 in posterior parietal cortex (CTBg) and 1 in visual area MT (FB)

title: cj84-fb-c15a
memo: FB injection near the ventral limit of area PGM (7m).
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj80-dy-c32a
memo: The DY injection was restricted to cytoarchitectural area PGM.
case_memo: This animal had injections directed to the posterior cingulate region. The right hemisphere (on the left of the images) had damage incurred during the surgery for injection but the injected hemisphere had no damage.

title: cj55-fe-c21a
memo: FE injection in the medial parietal cortex, area MIP according to registration to the Paxinos et al. 2012 atlas. However there was topographically organised label in the upper quadrant representation of various extrastriate areas, including DM, MT, V3, V4t, and MST. Based on what is known about the connections of MIP in the macaque, this suggests that the injection significantly included more caudal cortex (probably the dorsoanterior area, V3a), or that the atlas is incorrect about the extent of MIP in the marmoset. The presence of label in area 6DC (caudal dorsal premotor cortex), retroinsular cortex, and parietal area PE is compatible with involvement of MIP.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections in the posterior parietal region.

title: cj189nm-ctbr-c14c
memo: The CTB-red injection was placed in the caudal part of medial parietal area PGM, near the border with the medial visual cortex (area 19M). The pattern of label, which avoid most of the classical extrastriate cortex, indicates that area 19M was not included in the effective injection site.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj189-ctbr-c14c
memo: The CTB-red injection was placed in the caudal part of medial parietal area PGM, near the border with the medial visual cortex (area 19M). The pattern of label, which avoid most of the classical extrastriate cortex, indicates that area 19M was not included in the effective injection site.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj181-fb-c14d
memo: The FB injection was well centred in cytoarchitectural area TEO, mostly in the supragranular layers.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj181nm-fb-c14d
memo: The FB injection was well centred in cytoarchitectural area TEO, mostly in the supragranular layers.
case_memo: This animal had 2 sets of injections, in the prefrontal cortex and temporal lobe.

title: cj206-ctbr-c31a
memo: The CTBr injection was contained in area TEO. It only involved the supragranular layers and, to a smaller extent, layer 4. It encompassed an extensive dorsoventral region, along an elongated injection track.
case_memo: This animal received 4 tracer injections. The DY injection was in white matter, so it is not illustrated. The injection site is visible in section c29b.

title: cj77-fb-c25b
memo: The FB injection was large (a crystal of FB inserted in the cortex) but was restricted to cortex. It was centred in cytoarchitectural area OPt, but invaded the lateral intraparietal area (LIP) extensively, leading to widespread label in visual areas.
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections in posterior parietal cortex but the FE injection was ineffective.

title: cj203-ctbr-c15a
memo: The CTB-red injection  successfully penetrated the cortex of the shoulder of the calcarine sulcus, leading to a deposit of tracer that covered most layers of area 23V with little leakage into the subjacent white matter. The halo may have slightly encroached area 30, but if this happened the amount of contamination appears minimal. Of particular interest is the label in the representation of the far periphery of the visual field in multiple areas, including V1 and MT, and the extensive label in area prostriata. This reveals connections reciprocal to those reported by Palmer and Rosa (2006, Our J Neurosci 24: 2389–2405) confirming a visual function for area 23V.
case_memo: This animal received 4 injections, but only two satisfied the inclusion criteria: a DY injection in posterior parietal area PG, and a CTB-red injection in the retrosplenial cortex (area 23V).

title: cj203nm-ctbr-c15a
memo: The CTB-red injection  successfully penetrated the cortex of the shoulder of the calcarine sulcus, leading to a deposit of tracer that covered most layers of area 23V with little leakage into the subjacent white matter. The halo may have slightly encroached area 30, but if this happened the amount of contamination appears minimal. Of particular interest is the label in the representation of the far periphery of the visual field in multiple areas, including V1 and MT, and the extensive label in area prostriata. This reveals connections reciprocal to those reported by Palmer and Rosa (2006, Our J Neurosci 24: 2389–2405) confirming a visual function for area 23V.
case_memo: This animal received 4 injections, but only two satisfied the inclusion criteria: a DY injection in posterior parietal area PG, and a CTB-red injection in the retrosplenial cortex (area 23V).

title: cj215-dy-c28b
memo: The DY injection was centred on area prostriata. Some of the tracer was deposited in the white matter just adjacent to the calcarine sulcus, but there was no evidence of leakage up the track into parts of the parietal lobe.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective tracer injections

title: cj50-fr-c23a
memo: FR injection at the peripheral lower quadrant representation of area V4 (ventrolateral anterior area). Distribution of label indicates little or no involvement of adjacent parietal area Opt. Note more restricted distribution of label in the frontal and posterior cingulate regions, in comparison with the DY injection in PG/ OPt
case_memo: Animal with injections in the ventral part of the occipitoparietal transition cortex.

title: cj189-dy-c13b
memo: The diamidino yellow was well centred in area prostriata. There was no evidence of leakage up the track, and involvement of the white matter was minimal, and only adjacent to the cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj19-fe-m6a
memo: FE injection in the caudal part of the dorsoanterior area (DA/ V3a).
case_memo:
CJ19 was one of the first neuroanatomical tracing cases from the Rosa laboratory. At that stage we were very much in the process of learning how to process marmoset brain tissue, so the histology was...sub-optimal. There are no Nissls available, and an attempt at a gold chloride myelin stain (sections illustrated) is all that remained.
The cell plots in this case were performed manually using a camera lucida. Some of the original pencil plots are shown (sections m16a-16g). 
The registration to a template in this case was based on the brain external morphology only, since the histology was not compatible with the pipeline described by Majka et al. (2016; J Comp Neurol 524:2161–2181). Nonetheless, assignment of cells in the cortex to areas correlates very well with manual expert assessment, so the flat maps presented appear accurate.
The survival time (3 days) albeit short in comparison with later cases was well sufficient to result in clearly labeled cell bodies from both tracers.

title: w6dr-fr-c27b
memo: The FR injection was in the peripheral lower quadrant representation of area V4
case_memo:
This animal had a large V1 lesion in the left hemisphere, which encompassed the central and near-peripheral representations but spared the far periphery in the calcarine sulcus. The lesion was created at the age of 6 weeks postnatal.
After reaching adulthood this animal received 2 injections (FB and DY) in the left (V1 lesion) hemisphere. It also received FE and FR injections in the right (non-lesioned) hemisphere.

title: cj189nm-dy-c13b
memo: The diamidino yellow was well centred in area prostriata. There was no evidence of leakage up the track, and involvement of the white matter was minimal, and only adjacent to the cortex.
case_memo: This animal had 4 effective injections.

title: cj185-ctbr-c13c
memo: The CTB-red injection was restricted to area V4, lower quadrant representation. Note that this pattern of label is represented by one in 400 µm, not 1 in 200 µm as usual, due to substantial fading of the tracer in the alternate series.
case_memo: This animal had 4 injections, but only 3 are presented since a CTB-green injection in peripheral V1 revealed substantial white matter leakage, which led to labeled infra granular neurones in the central representations of various visual areas.

title: cj206-ctbgr-c27a
memo: The CTBgr injection was in the ventral part of area V3a. Based on registration to the template the caudal extent of the injection halo appears to have involved area V6, but this is not supported by the fact that there are no labeled neutrons in V1 (compare, e.g., with CJ52-FR, an adjacent V6 injection).
case_memo: This animal received 4 tracer injections. The DY injection was in white matter, so it is not illustrated. The injection site is visible in section c29b.

title: cj182-dy-c13a
memo: The DY injection was well centred in the representation of central vision in area V4 (ventrolateral anterior area), mostly in the supragranular and granular layers
case_memo: This animal had 3 effective injections in the rostral visual cortex and superior temporal region.

title: cj21-fb-9b
memo: The FB injection was located mostly within the dorsoanterior area (DA, or V3a), but crossed its caudal border with area DM (V6), leading to strong label in V1 near the upper vertical meridian representation. This was used as an example of injection involving the rostral border of DM in Rosa et al. 2005 (J Comp Neurol 483: 164-191; Fig. 12A).
case_memo:
This is an early case in which injections were combined with electrophysiology (see Figs. 13, 15 in Rosa and Tweedale 2000; J Comp Neurol 422: 621-651). Plots of labeled neurons were obtained for every second section (1 in 400 µm).
This case had damage near the midline (visible in sections 1-5) caused by a large injection of a third tracer (Fluorogold). This injection was not reconstructed electronically, but a manual record is available (Fig. 16 in the paper above). 
Registration of the V1/ V2 border was not optimal but the comparison of automated and expert-based distributions of labeled neurons to areas (compare with Rosa and Tweedale 2000) indicates that the results of the automated procedure are reliable throughout most, if not all of the labeled regions.

title: cj182-ctbgr-c13b
memo: CTB-green injection was in the representation of the lower quadrant in area V4 (ventrolateral anterior area).
case_memo: This animal had 3 effective injections in the rostral visual cortex and superior temporal region.

title: cj192-ctbr-c12b
memo: CTB-red was restricted to area V4 (ventrolateral anterior area), involving primarily the supra granular and granular layers in the central representation of the lower quadrant.
case_memo:
This animal had 4 tracer injections, of which 3 (DY, FB and CTB-red) were restricted to cortex, and 1 (CTB-green) included white matter. The same animal was also used to obtain electrophysiological recordings in a non-recovery experiment following the survival time required by the tracers; electrode tracks are visible in several sections. 
Some damage to the frontal lobe tissue occurred during extraction of the brain from the skull post-perfusion; this is evident between sections r4a-r5d (areas 12/ 47 and 8aV), and r5d-r8b (area 8b). This may have affected cell counts in these areas.

title: cj84-fr-c14c
memo: Small FR injection in the supragranular layers, near the ventral limit of area 19M.
case_memo: Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj21-dy-12c
memo: The DY injection was located in the currently poorly understood subdivision of cytoarchitectural area 19 that is located immediately ventral to the central upper quadrant representation in area DM (area 19 dorsointermediate, 19DI of Paxinos et al. 2012). This resulted in a distinct pattern of label in comparison with adjacent areas, which includes sparse label in V1, and frontal label that extends into the lateral orbitofrontal surface. Topographic analysis of the labeled patches in V1, V2 and MT indicates that this injection involved a central visual field representation near the horizontal meridian and upper quadrant.
case_memo:
This is an early case in which injections were combined with electrophysiology (see Figs. 13, 15 in Rosa and Tweedale 2000; J Comp Neurol 422: 621-651). Plots of labeled neurons were obtained for every second section (1 in 400 µm).
This case had damage near the midline (visible in sections 1-5) caused by a large injection of a third tracer (Fluorogold). This injection was not reconstructed electronically, but a manual record is available (Fig. 16 in the paper above). 
Registration of the V1/ V2 border was not optimal but the comparison of automated and expert-based distributions of labeled neurons to areas (compare with Rosa and Tweedale 2000) indicates that the results of the automated procedure are reliable throughout most, if not all of the labeled regions.

title: cj210-ctbgr-c23a
memo: The CTB-green injection was contained in the peripheral lower quadrant representation of area V6 (dorsomedial area).
case_memo: This animal had 4 tracer injections, but the DY injection was not plotted given extensive track left in the white matter (visible in section c27b).

title: cj52x-fr-c11b
memo: FR injection at the rostral border of area DM, in the upper quadrant representation. Manual reconstruction of this case was illustrated in Figure 7 of Rosa et al. 2009 (J Neurosci 29:4548–4563)
case_memo:
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

This case underwent a microsimulation experiment, so electrode tracks can be seen within and around the premotor areas.

Quality of Nissl stain is poor in some frontal sections, which led to suboptimal registration to the template in the anterior temporal cortex. In particular, parcellation in sections r10a and r10b was partially removed as the low quality of staining in these regions precluded accurate registration. However, this has not affected assignment of neurons to areas since there were no labelled cells in the anterior temporal cortex.

title: cj52x-fe-c10b
memo: FE injection restricted to the lower quadrant representation in area DM. Manual reconstruction of this case was illustrated in Figure 10 of Rosa et al. 2009 (J Neurosci 29:4548–4563).
case_memo:
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj36-fb-s9a
memo: FB injection in the caudal part of the dorsomedial area (DM). Manual reconstruction of this case was illustrated in Figure 8 of Rosa et al. 2009 (J Neurosci 29:4548–4563).
case_memo:
In this case the FB labeled neurones were plotted in every second section, whereas the FR labeled neurones were plotted for every section.
The  parcellation into anatomical structures should be considered approximate in sections s1a and s2a. The misregistration occurred as these sections are first images in the stack which caused difficulties in matching with the atlas close to the midline.
This animal also had a DY injection visible around section s5b, which was not included in the present data set due to extensive invasion of white matter as well as extensive fading by the time of plotting. A partial data set for this injection (label in frontal lobe) is illustrated in Figure 11 of Burman et al. 2006 (J Comp Neurol 495:149–172).

title: cj81-fr-c20b
memo: FB and FR injectons in the peripheral representation, along the midline portion of V2. Both injections were located near the border with V1.
case_memo:
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

Part of the right hemisphere was removed immediately prior to perfusion to obtain material for an attempted brain slice experiment.

title: cj82-dy-c18a
memo: DY injection in V2, midline, near V1 border, at the peripheral representation lower field (~20˚ eccentricity).
case_memo:
This case attempted to create a series of injections in area V1, exploring the connections of central and peripheral visual field representations. Part of the right hemisphere was removed immediately prior to perfusion to obtain material for an attempted brain slice experiment. 
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj90-fr-c9a
memo: FR injection in representation of near peripheral visual field. Involved all layers.
case_memo: This case had 2 tracer injections in area V2. Note long survival time for transport.

title: cj90-dy-c9a
memo: Small DY injection in the supragranular layers of V2 near V1 border.
case_memo: This case had 2 tracer injections in area V2. Note long survival time for transport.

title: cj82-fr-c14b
memo: FR injection in V1, near V2 border, in peripheral vision representation (~10˚ lower field).
case_memo:
This case attempted to create a series of injections in area V1, exploring the connections of central and peripheral visual field representations. Part of the right hemisphere was removed immediately prior to perfusion to obtain material for an attempted brain slice experiment. 
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj178-fb-c6d
memo: The FB injection in this case was centred on the dorsal bank of the calcimine sulcus. There was no invasion of the ventral bank, but the injection resulted in a large area of necrosis in the occipital white matter and dorsal surface, which may have masked some connections, particularly with V2.
case_memo: This animal was part of a study of prefrontal cortex connections, but also had an attempted injection in the peripheral representation of V1.

title: cj82-fe-c6b
memo: Small FE injection in the central visual field representation of V1, lower quadrant.
case_memo:
This case attempted to create a series of injections in area V1, exploring the connections of central and peripheral visual field representations. Part of the right hemisphere was removed immediately prior to perfusion to obtain material for an attempted brain slice experiment. 
Note: injections were in left hemisphere, images are flipped for consistency with other cases.

title: cj174-fb-c5a
memo: The FB injection was large. It was centred on the upper bank of the calcimine sulcus, but included the supragranular layers of the ventral bank as well. Leakage up the track was minimal, and any invasion of white matter at this level of the brain would correspond to axons leading to V1. the paucity of label in the occipital lobe surface indicates little or no contamination by leakage.
case_memo: This case had 3 good injections in the primary visual area (V1). A DY injection in the medial part of V1/ V2 was not analysed due to extensive invasion of the white matter (this injection is visible in section c6a).

title: cj174-ctbgr-c3a
memo: The CTB-green injection was located near the representation of the fovea in V1. It only involved supragranular layers.
case_memo: This case had 3 good injections in the primary visual area (V1). A DY injection in the medial part of V1/ V2 was not analysed due to extensive invasion of the white matter (this injection is visible in section c6a).

title: cj174-ctbr-c2d
memo: The CTB-red injection was very small, and restricted to the supragranular layers of V1.
case_memo: This case had 3 good injections in the primary visual area (V1). A DY injection in the medial part of V1/ V2 was not analysed due to extensive invasion of the white matter (this injection is visible in section c6a).
